data.description: Terrific renovation opportunity of classic Parkview Wardman.  The classic Wardman or "Front-Porch" row house,  circa 1907 were all originally designed by architect Nicholas Grimm.  613 Princeton Place is reminiscent of the classics with a traditional three window front with large porch.  The interior remains classically in tact with the formal front parlor or original living room,  then formal dining room with a breakfast room or porch in the rear that  opens to back yard.  Basement  is partially finished with walk to rear and remaining original garage.  Upstairs features the traditional bedrooms.  Wonderful opportunity to create your dream home or develop into two, 2,000+ two level condominium units.  The 600 block of Princeton Place is a quiet tree lined street adjacent to the Soldier's home.  A wonderful starter home in a neighborhood rich in history.  3 block walk to metro. Ask agent about 6.5% interest rate and buy down options
